constructor: special member that is called when an object is created

used to set default or user-defined values for object attributes

> default
* constructor has no parameters
* if no constructor is explicitly defined then java provides by default
* code
class A {

    //default
    A(){
        System.out.println("default!");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        A a = new A();
    }
}

> parameterized
* constructor with parameters
* used when we wish to initialize the fields of class with our own values
* code
class B{
    String name;
    int id;

    B(String name, int id){
        this.name = name;
        this.id = id;
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        B b = new B("Adams", 53);
    }
}

> private
* code
public class PrivateConstructorClass{
    private PrivateConstructorClass(){
        
    }
}
